<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Patch>
  <!--
    Package 14B XML hygiene fix.

    This safety patch is intentionally disabled for now.

    Reason:
    The previous version added explicit <thingCategories> to many ThingDefs whenever
    the node was not present directly on the child def. In RimWorld XML this is unsafe
    for defs that inherit from parents such as BaseHumanMakeableGun, BaseMeleeWeapon,
    BaseApparel, ResourceBase, BodyPartBase, etc. Those parents can already provide
    categories through inheritance, so adding the same category on the child produces
    load-time errors such as:
      "has duplicate thingCategory WeaponsRanged"
      "has duplicate thingCategory BodyPartsBionic"

    Leaving this Patch file present but empty avoids missing-file/order surprises while
    removing the over-broad duplicate-category behavior. If a specific item later proves
    unstorable, fix that exact ThingDef or add a narrow conditional patch for that one
    def only, not a broad inherited-def category sweep.
  -->
</Patch>
